[Black "The Pawns"]
[Result "*"]

{ Let's talk about the role of your pawns! Your pawns should enable your major pieces to develop smoothly. Once your pawns have taken their place in the center, additional pawn moves are generally not needed.  This is because you already opened the lines for all your other pieces to join the battle. An exception would be when an opportunity arises to push one of your opponent's pieces to a less favorable square, like in the situation here @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pppp1ppp/5n2/8/3QP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNB1KB1R w KQkq - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6.e5  . }
