[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5
{ Let's add another layer to determining which knight to develop first.  First, bring out the knight that pressures your opponent's central pawn.  So, in this given scenario, you'd choose @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/4p3/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq e6 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Nf3  .   Similarly, in this position, you'd go for @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp2pppp/5n2/3p4/2PP4/8/PP3PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 1 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nc3  .   However, if your opponent is already attacking your central pawn, you should move your knight to defend your central pawn.  For instance, in this position as Black, you'd opt for @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/4p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2@@EndFEN@@  2...Nc6  . }
