[Black "The Bishops"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 -- 2. d4 -- 3. Nf3 -- 4. Nc3
{ Now let's talk about the bishops.    Following the knights' development, your next priority should be to develop the bishops. This is because, generally, it's not feasible to activate the rooks early, and advancing the queen too soon can be risky, as it's your most valuable piece. Your opponent could accelerate their development by threatening your queen.    Unlike the knights, the optimal squares for developing bishops vary across openings. }
