[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Repertoire Specific Rules"]
[Black "The King"]
[Result "*"]

{ Let's talk about the king's role:   During the game's opening phase, quickly securing your king, typically through castling, is vital. With both sides starting with their full array of pieces, the king's safety is key. In endgames, when many pieces have been traded off, the king can adopt a more active role.   Remember this crucial rule: If your king is safer, keep the queens on the board. If your king is less safe, aim to trade queens. }
