[White "Quickstarter for White - Open Games 1.e4 e5  "]
[Black "Petrov 3...Nc6 and 4...Bb4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 { Golden Rule Number One: place your pawns in the center. } 1... e5
{ Black is copying your strategy! } 2. Nf3 Nf6
{ The Petrov Defense! This is a solid opening choice for Black, aiming to contest the center right from the beginning. Good news! I recommend a solution where you will often transpose back to the Scotch Opening. The advantage of this strategy is that you can stay within a familiar territory, avoiding the main lines of the Petrov Defense. }
3. Nc3
{ You develop the knight and defend your central pawn. This simple move will likely bring you back to the Scotch opening.   3.Nxe5  is the most played move when Black first kicks back your knight with  3...d6  4.Nf3  and then also wins your central pawn with  4...Nxe4   @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppp1ppp/5n2/4p3/4P3/2N2N2/PPPP1PPP/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3.d4  is also an alternative which I am recommending in my Attacking Repertoire for Club Players. }
3... Nc6 4. d4
{ The Four Knights Scotch. You use the first golden rule and place the pawn in the center.  After  4...exd4  5.Nxd4  , you are back in your Scotch theory and managed to deal with the Petrov opening without studying much more theory. }
4... Bb4 { Black goes for a pin on the knight } 5. Nxe5
{ You capture the pawn with the knight. Capturing with the knight opens the diagonal for the queen, which can come in handy. }
5... Nxe4 { Black captures your pawn. } 6. Qg4
{ Double attack on the knight and g7-pawn. This is why you captured your knight on the previous move.  @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n2n2/4p3/1b1PP3/2N2N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 1 5@@EndFEN@@  5.dxe5?  Nxe4  would keep your queen blocked, but @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n2n2/4p3/1b1PP3/2N2N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 1 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nxe5  Nxe4  allows the  6.Qg4  double attack.  White is doing excellent here, but take some time to study the further details of this line because after @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n5/4N3/1b1Pn1Q1/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1B1KB1R b KQkq - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Nxc3  7.Qxg7  Rf8  8.a3  is a thematic idea to counterattack the bishop. }
