[White "Quickstarter for White - Sicilian "]
[Black "Silician: Four knights"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5
{ This move marks the Sicilian Defense. Black does not put a pawn directly in the center but controls it instead with a flank pawn. }
2. Nf3
{ You play in the same fashion as in the Open Games after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq e3 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...e5  2.Nf3  You develop the knight and control the center.  Wait to put your other pawn in the center with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq e3 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...c5  2.d4  because after  2...cxd4  3.Qxd4  Black can develop with tempo and attack your queen with  3...Nc6  . }
2... e6
{ Black opens up the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop and controls the d5-square. }
3. d4 { The Open Sicilian. } 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4
{ You capture with the knight as usual! } 4... Nc6 5. Nc3 Nf6
{ This is the Four Knights Sicilian.  After  5...Bb4  , you can punish Black with a clearance tactic  6.Nxc6  bxc6  7.Qd4  with a double attack on the bishop and g7-pawn. It is also fine to continue the Robust Development Setup with  6.Be2  when after  6...Nf6  7.O-O  you transpose back to the Four Knights Sicilian }
6. Be2 { You develop as planned. } 6... Bb4 7. O-O
{ In the Robust Development Setup, it's common to sacrifice one or two pawns and get a powerful attack in return. Don't get fooled that your setup may not be working because it seems to lose a pawn. It's time to show the thematic ideas for your attack when Black is going for the pawn. }
7... Bxc3
{ Black is more or less forced to eliminate the knight and go after the pawn. }
8. bxc3 Nxe4
{ Black enters the Poisoned Pawns variation! When Black plays ... Nxe4, you also want to play Qg4, so you move the bishop out of the way first. }
9. Bd3
{ This idea has been used by Caruana and Dubov.  When Black's knight captures the e4-pawn, you like to counter with Qg4 as in the pin variation.  You sacrifice another pawn with  9...Nxc3  and after  10.Qg4  O-O  11.Bb2  , you get a powerful attack with your queen and bishop aimed at the king. Also @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pp1p1ppp/2n1p3/8/3Nn3/2PB4/P1P2PPP/R1BQ1RK1 b kq - 1 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Nf6  can't stop your attack since  10.Ba3  is powerful and prevents Black from castling. }
