[White "Quickstarter for White - Scandinavian and Sidelines"]
[Black "Nimzowitsch Defense"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4
{ Get ready to tackle the sidelines! What's going to be super helpful here is everything you've learned from the course. It's good to get your pawns in the middle. Remember, you usually develop the knights first, and hunting your opponents' knights can be smart. Sometimes, you'll play against opponents who don't know their openings well and do something offbeat. If that happens, stay calm. Use the concepts you've learned to take advantage of their unusual start. }
1... Nc6 2. d4 { You take the center! } 2... d5 3. exd5 { You trade as always }
3... Qxd5 4. Nf3 { You develop the knight and defend your central pawn. } 4...
Bg4 5. Nc3 { You develop the other knight and attack the queen. } 5... Qh5
{ The only good move for Black! } 6. d5 { You start hunting the knight } 6...
O-O-O 7. Be2 { You develop the bishop and support the knight! } 7... e6 8. O-O
{ Also  8.Ng5  is a good alternative! } 8... exd5 9. h3
{ You start chasing away the bishop! You will either win your pawn back or get a powerful initiative. Study the lines further from here.  A lot of Club Players went wrong here with  9...Bxh3?  when  10.Ng5  wins the knight with the discovered attack, even without damaging your pawn structure. }
