[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter for Black vs. Italian and Ruy Lopez "]
[Black "Four Knights Italian: 4.Nc3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 { Overwhelmingly the most popular move at the club player level. } 1...
e5
{ Prepare to begin with the Black pieces. Even though you haven't learned any moves from the Black side yet, you already understand the concepts from studying the moves from the White side. The principles of the opening stay the same. Your priority is controlling the center with pawns, and you do that from your first move. }
2. Nf3 { White develops and attacks your central pawn! } 2... Nc6
{ It's time to develop and defend the pawn. } 3. Bc4
{ This is the Italian Game, a very popular choice at the beginner level. White plans to castle quickly and points the bishop towards your f7-pawn. }
3... Nf6
{ Applying what you've learned, you start by developing your knights before moving on to your bishops. }
4. Nc3
{ White develops the other knight. A common move at the Beginner level. } 4...
Nxe4
{ You are going for a tactic! You don't give up the knight for free. After White captures you, you can place your pawn in the center with a fork to regain the piece. Usually, when White goes for this, they are not too well-prepared, so you learn some fascinating variations and develop tactics to take your opponent down early on. }
5. Nxe4 d5 { Forking the bishop and knight } 6. Bxd5
{ A common mistake at the beginner level is to capture the pawn. The light-squared bishop is the strongest minor piece in the Italian opening, and you are happy to get the bishop. }
6... Qxd5 { You capture the bishop. } 7. Nc3 Qa5
{ You shift your queen, leaving the diagonal open for both bishops. You also keep the option of castling queenside. Next, you aim to pin the knight with ...Bg4 and then castle queenside.  Another strong move could be  7...Qd6  , as suggested in my Attacking Repertoire for Club Players for Black. }
8. O-O Bg4
{ You create a powerful pin on the knight. As White has already traded their light-squared bishop, they can't use their bishop on e2 to break the pin. }
