4... Nxd4
{ This move, taking your knight, is a mistake that is still quite frequently played. It helps you by letting you get your queen active, but Black doesn't get anything in return. }
5. Qxd4 { Your queen is powerful in the center. } 5... d6
{ A popular move at the club level. Black opens a path for their light bishop and protects against your e5 attack, so they can safely develop their knight with ...Nf6. }
6. Nc3
{ As usual you develop the knights first and you prepare to castle on the queenside. With the d-file semi-open, your rook will be immediately active after castling queenside. }
