{ You develop the bishop, getting ready to castle on the queenside.   7.Bg5  would pin the knight, but it's not a big problem for Black as they can unpin with  7...Be7  .  Trading your bishop for their knight is bad, as after  8.Bxf6  Bxf6  , Black's bishop, becomes very active. }
7... Be7 { Black develops and prepares to castle. } 8. O-O-O
{ You follow the third golden rule and castle. Next, you want to play e5 and open up the d-file!  You have punished the @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/8/3NP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4...Nxd4  mistake from Black in the most effective way by castling queenside quickly and having a powerful rook on the d-file which will open up soon. }
8... O-O 9. Kb1 Be6 10. f3
{ This is a useful move to solidify your center. Now you are ready to start an attack on the kingside with h4 and g4. Since you have more control in the center you also have better chances in the attack! }
