5... Bb6 6. Nc3 Nf6
{ This pin setup is to continue development with Bd3, O-O and in the end pin the knight with Bg5. }
7. Bd3 { Your bishop supports the central pawn! } 7... O-O 8. O-O
{ You follow the second golden rule and safeguard the king by castling. } 8...
d6 9. Bg5
{ The pin has the potential to destroy Black's king's safety. The pin immobilizes the knight, and it's strong to add an attacker with Nd5 aiming to destroy Black's pawn structure in front of the king.  If Black tries to break the pin with  9...h6  , you should keep it with  10.Bh4 }
