{ You launch an attack on Black's queen while opening the b2-f6 diagonal for your dark-squared bishop. This strategic move sets you up to continue with Re1 and Bb2, further enhancing your control over the board.  The optimal position for Black's queen in this situation is on d6. Therefore, if Black moves their queen to d6 with  11...Qd6  , you have a strong follow-up with  12.c5  .  This move effectively forces the queen to move again, disrupting Black's setup and gaining more space and control in the center. }
