15... gxf6 16. Qe3 { You get your queen into the attack. } 16... Kh8
{ The only good move for Black to defend against the mate and prepare to get the rook to the g-file. }
17. Nd4
{ You're targeting Black's bishop and aiming to take control of the f5 square. This move sets you up to play Qh6, forcing Black to push their pawn with ...f5.  Playing  17.Qh6  right away is also a reasonable option, but it doesn't put as much pressure on Black since they can defend with  17...f5  followed by  18.Rxa3  Rg8 }
17... Rg8 18. Nxe6 { You capture the bishop! } 18... fxe6 19. Qxe6 Bb4
{ It looks logical to defend the passed pawn, but this blunders an important pawn. }
20. Bxh7 { You will win back the other bishop with a fork. } 20... Kxh7 21.
Qh3+ Kg7 22. Qg4+ { Forking the king and bishop. } 22... Kf7 23. Qxb4
{ You will also pick up the a3-pawn with a winning middlegame. } *

