Nxe4 { Capturing is inaccurate for Black. } 19. Rce1
{ It's time for the pin! You want to keep your other rook on the f-file to win the d4-pawn later. }
19... Nf6 20. Rxe8+ Nxe8 21. Rf4
{ Now that you have chased Black's knight to a bad position you can win the central pawn back. }
21... Nf6 22. Rxd4
{ In this endgame, you have a superior pawn structure. Your plan to play Nc5 is strategic, utilizing a strong square and setting up potential tactical opportunities. Depending on Black's response, you have a couple of effective plans. One option is to play Rd6, targeting the c6-pawn. This move can put significant pressure on Black and potentially win you a crucial pawn. Alternatively, you can play Ra4, which would keep Black's rook tied down in defense of the a7-pawn. This move restricts Black's activity and can give you more control over the game. }
