7... Nxe5 8. dxe5 Qxe5 9. O-O
{ You get your king to safety. You would be happy when White captures the c3-pawn since it opens a powerful diagonal for your bishop. }
9... Qxc3 10. Rb1
{ With Rb3 and Bb2 coming, Black is in big danger. Your bishops, rook, and queen will all be positioned well to start targeting Black's king. Meanwhile Black is still underdeveloped. }
