{ You go for the standard plan to castle queenside. } 8... O-O 9. O-O-O Bxc3
{ Black can immediately capture the knight to win the central pawn. } 10. Bxc3
Qf4+ 11. Rd2 { You support the f2-pawn. } 11... Nxe4
{ Black can't capture the pawn and attack the pinned rook. } 12. Qd4
{ You are threatening mate and pinning the knight. } 12... f6 13. f3
{ Pins and wins the knight. Attacking the pinned knight with  13.Bd3  also works.  Usually, it is best to attack with a piece from a lower value so that if Black still adds a defender, you can win the knight in return for the pawn. }
