5. Be2 { You close the e-file to prevent Black from harassing your king. } 5...
Re8 { Skewer on the knight and pawn. } 6. Ng4
{ A move that rarely has been played before. In the only game, Grandmaster Paravyan won against Grandmaster Injic.  The idea is that you would like to trade your knight, because with  6.Nf3  , it's blocking a powerful square for your bishop, and after  6.Nd3  , when Black wins the pawn back with  6...Bxc3  7.dxc3  Nxe4  your knight is also misplaced since it's blocking your queen on the d-file.  @@StartFEN@@rnbqr1k1/pppp1ppp/5n2/4N3/1b2P3/2N5/PPPPBPPP/R1BQK2R w KQ - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Nd3  or  6.Nf3  are much more common and sound alternatives. }
6... Nxg4 { Black could trade the knight to win the e4-pawn after. } 7. Bxg4
Bxc3
{ Black eliminates the knight and prepares to win the e4-pawn.  This would transpose to the @@StartFEN@@rnbqr1k1/pppp1ppp/5n2/8/1b2P1N1/2N5/PPPPBPPP/R1BQK2R b KQ - 4 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Bxc3  7.dxc3  Nxg4  8.Bxg4  variation. }
8. dxc3 Rxe4+ 9. Be2
{ You go back and block the attack. You get ready to castle quickly. The point of the @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/pppp1ppp/5n2/4N3/1b2P3/2N5/PPPP1PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQ - 1 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Ng4  move  is that you can continue with Be3, Qd2 and O-O-O, which would have been the case in the mainline with  5.Nd3  . }
9... Qe7
{ Black could add another attacker to your pinned bishop, but this is not dangerous. }
10. Be3 { You block the e-file. Your bishops are working well together. } 10...
Nc6 11. Qd2
{ A cunning move! You don't rush to caste with  11.O-O  as a queenside castle is stronger when you get your rook to the open d-file, allowing you to get your rooks to the center quickly. }
11... d6 12. h3
{ Another cunning move. Instead of rushing with  12.O-O-O  , make sure to keep the bishop pair. The problem is that castling immediately gives Black a chance to trade off the bishops with  12...Bg4  . }
12... Bf5 13. O-O-O
{ You get your king to safety and already threaten to win material with Bd3 going after the rook and bishop.  When Black anticipates this and goes for  13...Re8  , you can play  14.Rhe1  , getting your rook to the center. Now that all your pieces are well-placed, you can march your pawns on the kingside and start an attack. }
