[White "2a) Petrov and Philidor Defenses "]
[Black "Philidor 3...Nd7 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 { The Philidor variation. } 3. d4 Nd7 4. dxe5
{ The usual rule is that when pawns face each other in the center, you trade!  4.Nc3  would also be a sound alternative. }
4... dxe5 5. Nc3 { You develop the knights first, as usual. } 5... c6
{ The most popular move at the beginner level, but this is dangerous as Black is slow with development. }
6. Bc4 { You eye at the f7-pawn and are ready to attack with Ng5 next } 6...
Be7 7. Ng5
{ You can use a neat trick to get the pair of bishops! You go all out for the attack on the f7-pawn. }
7... Bxg5 { Black captures your knight. } 8. Qh5
{ Double attack! You threaten mate and the bishop. } 8... Qe7 9. Qxg5
{ You gain the powerful bishop pair in an open position. } *

[Event "?"]
