{ The usual rule is that when pawns face each other in the center, you trade!  4.Nc3  would also be a sound alternative. }
4... dxe5 5. Nc3 { You develop the knights first, as usual. } 5... Ngf6 6. Bc4
{ Your bishop sits nicely on c4, aiming at the f7-pawn. Your next goal is to castle. After that, you can play Qe2 and Rd1 to get your rook to control the open d-file. }
6... Be7 { Black mostly wants to play it safer and keeps the bishop on e7. } 7.
O-O O-O 8. Qe2
{ You can follow a similar plan and put your rook on the open d-file.  Usually, it's a good idea to respond to  8...c6  with  9.a4  , to stop Black from gaining more space on the queenside with ...b5. }
