{ This idea has been used by Caruana and Dubov. When Black's knight captures the e4-pawn, you like to counter with Qg4 as in the pin variation.   9.Nxc6  is also an alternative but not consistent with the other variations in your repertoire. }
9... Nxc3 { The most popular move by club players, grabbing another pawn. } 10.
Qg4 { You bring the queen to g4 and harass the g7-pawn. } 10... Qf6 11. Nxc6
{ It's time to trade the knights. } 11... bxc6
{ Black can also capture back with the other pawn, but you should reply similarly. }
