{ Just as in the Kan, you can shrug your shoulders on the e4-pawn.  When Black doesn't go for the pawn and plays  7...O-O  , you can play  8.Nxc6  bxc6  9.e5  chasing away the knight. This motif only worked for you after castling, because if you played @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pp1p1ppp/2n1pn2/8/1b1NP3/2N5/PPP1BPPP/R1BQK2R w KQkq - 5 7@@EndFEN@@  7.Nxc6  bxc6  8.e5  Black has  8...Nxe4  attacking the pinned knight on c3. }
