[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3b) Sicilian Four Knights, Taimanov and Kan Variations"]
[Black "Sicilian: Kan Variation #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5
{ This move marks the Sicilian Defense. Black does not put a pawn directly in the center but controls it instead with a flank pawn. }
2. Nf3
{ You play in the same fashion as in the Open Games after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq e3 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...e5  2.Nf3  You develop the knight and control the center.  Wait to put your other pawn in the center with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq e3 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...c5  2.d4  because after  2...cxd4  3.Qxd4  Black can develop with tempo and attack your queen with  3...Nc6  . }
2... e6
{ Black opens up the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop and controls the d5-square. }
3. d4 { The Open Sicilian. } 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6
{ This is the Kan Sicilian, named after the Soviet international master Ilya Kan. Black is looking to play his pawn to b5 early on and without Nc6. }
5. Nc3
{ White develops his knights first and is ready to continue with the robust development setup Be2, O-O, Be3. }
5... b5
{ Black is gaining space on the queenside and prepares for ...Bb7 and ...b4 }
6. Be2 Bb7 7. O-O
{ You are not impressed with Black's threats and keep the Robust Development Setup. }
7... b4 { Black goes after the e4-pawn. } 8. Na4 Bxe4 9. Bf3
{ It's time to control the diagonal and target the rook in the corner. } 9...
Nf6 { Black develops and defends the bishop. } 10. Bxe4 Nxe4 11. Re1
{ You bring the rook to the center, gaining a tempo on the knight! } 11... d5
12. c4
{ You undermine Black's center! Black has to capture en-passant.   12...Be7?  13.cxd5  exd5  14.Nf5  O-O  15.Qxd5!  Forks the rook and knight, and after  15...Qxd5  16.Nxe7+  picks up the bishop and wins the queen back with a royal fork. }
12... bxc3 13. Nxc3 Nxc3 14. Qh5
{ And ''Boom'' says the dynamite! You are pinning the f7 and e6-pawns. Nxe6 is on the agenda. }
14... Ne4
{ 14...g6  would be losing for Black.  15.Qe5  Rg8  16.Nxe6  and the e-file opens with a devastating effect. }
15. Nxe6 g6 16. Nc7+ { Thematic to win the d5-pawn with the queen. } 16... Qxc7
17. Qxd5 f5 18. Qxa8
{ And you win the rook in the corner. After  18...Bb4  , you have two options. I like to continue the energetic play with  19.Rxe4+  fxe4  20.Bh6  , which prevents Black from castling and threatens Rc1. Black's only move is to stop that with  20...e3  when after  21.fxe3  , you can start harassing Black's king with Qe4+.  Also  19.Re2  would be a good alternative. }
