10... b6 11. Bc4 Bb7 12. Qe2
{ You support the bishop, and get ready to play Rfd1 and pressure the d6-pawn. Also, you keep an eye on the a6-pawn, making it impossible for Black's rook to move to the c-file. Black has to use a tactic now to get a fine position. }
