14. Bxf6 Nxf6 15. Nh4
{ I love the plan here! You want to play Nf5 and get a powerful knight there. After that, you can play Ne3 and Bd5 when both your knights are ready to dominate on the d5-square. You use one to trade the knight on f6 and the other to dominate. }
