{ Black accepts the challenge. } 9. bxc3 Nxe4 10. Bd3
{ You have seen this idea before. } 10... Nf6
{ Black resists the temptation to capture another poisoned pawn and retreats. }
11. Ba3
{ You develop the bishop and prevent Black from castling. This issue is not going to be fixed easily for Black.  After  11...Qc7  12.Re1  d6  Black blocks the bishop's diagonal but moves the bishop with  13.Bb5  adds the queen as an extra attacker.  13...O-O?  now lead to  14.Bxd6  forking the queen and rook. So instead Black should defend with the desperate  13...Ke7   Also after @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/pp1p1ppp/1qn1p3/8/4n3/1NPB4/P1P2PPP/R1BQ1RK1 b kq - 1 10@@EndFEN@@  10...d5  11.Ba3  is strong, preventing Black from castling. }
