10... Qd7
{ One of the most critical moves Black can play aiming to double on the d-file also preventing your play with h3 and g4 }
11. h3 { You still kick away the bishop. } 11... Bh5 12. Be2
{ You will start preparing for a Qb3 followed by a discovered attack with Ne5 aiming at the bishop.   12.g4?  would be a big mistake now because after  12...Nxg4  13.hxg4  Qxg4+  , you lose the piece back. }
12... Rad8 { Black can bring the rook to the center! } 13. Qb3
{ You move the queen out of the way. } 13... Rfe8
{ Black also brings the other rook to the center! } 14. Ne5
{ You go to the center! } 14... Nxe5 15. Bxh5
{ The idea is that in case Black eventually captures back your bishop, the knight will be misplaced. }
