{ Black escapes with the bishop. } 16. O-O
{ You stay consistent with your previous plan and castle. } 16... Bxh4
{ It looks like a free pawn for Black, but the pawn is poisoned. Black should not capture the pawn but play something to attack your strong knight, like  16...Bf6  , after which you can play  17.g5  , forcing  17...Bxe5  18.dxe5  and you keep the bishop pair. }
17. g5 { You want to trap the bishop! } 17... Bxg5 18. Qg4 { Double attack! }
18... Bxe3 19. Bxf7+
