11... Nbd5 12. Bg5 Bd7 13. Bxf6
{ After the trade, you are ready to go for the d5-break. } 13... Nxf6
{ If Black plays  13...Bxf6  instead, you will win a pawn with  14.Nxd5  exd5  15.Bxd5  . }
14. d5 exd5 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16. Nxf7
{ And it's time to strike!  The sacrifice on f7 is often very strong in this opening. The fact that  16...Kxf7  is the best move, showing how crushing White's position is after  17.Qxd5+  Kg6  18.Qe4+  Kh6  19.Qxe7  , you are a pawn up and infiltrate Black's seventh rank. }
16... Rxf7
{ For this move, finding the crushing continuation may be more difficult. } 17.
Qxd5 Be8 18. Qxb7
{ You have the pin on the rook and the bishop! You should win at least a full rook and have a dominating advantage. }
