{ When Black captures your knight, you have a beautiful move! } 9. Bc4
{ This is powerful! You threaten Bxf7, and Black's knight can't escape.  After  9...Ne4?  10.Bxf7+  Kd7  11.Qe6+  would already win the knight back with a fork! Despite that, the computer suggests that  11.O-O  is even more winning for White. }
9... e6
{ Black defends against the threat! Now that Black played both ...e6 and ...g6, the dark-squares are weak. }
10. bxc3 Bg7 11. Ba3 { You make use of it not allowing Black to castle. } 11...
Na5 { Black can aim for the fork instead. } 12. Bb5+
{ By giving a check, you make sure Black can't trade your light-squared bishop for the knight }
12... Bd7 13. Qb2
{ You drop back with the queen! Black can't still castle because of your bishop. }
