13... Qd6
{ Blocking with the queen also allows you to trade the knights and force Black to take back with the pawn. }
14. Nxd5+ exd5 15. Qxb5
{ You catch the knight and again manage to avoid the trade of queens. } 15...
Rb8 16. Qd3 { You bring the queen back! } 16... f6
{ Black's best move is to create a safer spot for the king on f7. } 17. O-O Kf7
18. Be3
{ You develop the bishop and are ready to add an attacker to the d5-pawn. }
18... Rxb2
{ Black could capture the pawn, but you will get the b-file and a rook on the seventh rank. }
19. Rab1 { You control the b-file.  19.Rfb1  is just a as good } 19... Rxb1 20.
Rxb1
{ Next move you will play Rb7! You are about to win the a7-pawn back and will likely get an endgame where your passed a-pawn gives good chances. }
