{ You offer a trade of bishops. } 9... Bxg2 10. Kxg2 Nbd7 11. Qf3
{ You make sure your queen controls the long diagonal now. } 11... Rc8 12. Bf4
{ You develop your bishop and start threatening discovered attack!  Grabbing a pawn with  12...Qxd4  would be way to dangerous for Black since you can dominate the open d-file with  13.Rfd1 }
