10... Be6 11. Ne3 g6 12. h4
{ You push forward for the attack! Many moves are possible here. Giri opted for  12.O-O-O  in the game against Artiemiev but after the precise  12...Bh6  13.Kb1  Bxe3  14.Qxe3  Ng4  15.Qe1  Nxe5  16.Qxe5  O-O  , Giri didn't manage to break through the position, and the game ended in a draw. }
12... h5
{ Black stops your pawn!  When Black plays  12...Bg7  , you continue your plan with  13.h5  and  13...Nxh5  runs into  14.Rxh5  when the bishop on g7 is still hanging. }
13. d5 { You can now force a better endgame with a pawn-up. } 13... Nbxd5 14.
Ncxd5 Bxd5 15. Nxd5 Qxd5 16. Qxd5
{ All the trades are forced as Black's knight is pinned. } 16... cxd5 17. Bb5+
Kd8 18. O-O-O { You get your rook on the powerful d-file and win the d5-pawn. }
18... Bg7 19. Bxf6 Bxf6 20. Rxd5+ { Your rook will enter the seventh rank. }
20... Kc7 21. Rd7+ Kb6 22. Bc4
