8... Nbd7 { When Black develops the knight this allow the immediate e5! } 9. e5
dxe5 10. dxe5 Ng4 11. Bxg7 Kxg7 12. Qf4
{ And you kick the knight away with a dominating advantage!  Another reason why @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/p3ppbp/2pp1npB/1p6/3PP3/2N2N2/PPPQ1PPP/R3KB1R w KQ b6 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8.a3  is better than  8.Bd3  is that in this specific variation, you had your bishop on d3 Black can still equalize with a tactical trick! @@StartFEN@@r1bq1r2/p2nppkp/2p3p1/1p2P3/5Qn1/2NB1N2/PPP2PPP/R3K2R b KQ - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Ngxe5  13.Nxe5  Qc7  pins and wins the knight back because you don't have the Nd3 retreat available to support your queen. }
