{ You follow the standard plan and develop the knights first, as usual. The Pirc opening gives White many ways to play.   4.f4  would also be an alternative to gain a bigger center, or you could opt for  4.Bg5  or  4.Be3  . }
4... Bg7 5. Bg5
{ Only the fifth most popular move in the position, but one that fits the style to start the direct battle. You would like to start hunting Black's knight with e5, but to prepare for that, you first want to connect your rook and queen.   5.e5?  is bad because after  5...dxe5  6.dxe5  Qxd1+  , you have to make a sad choice to either retreat your knight back or capture with your king and give up your right to castle.  After @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp1ppbp/3p1np1/8/3PP3/2N2N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 2 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Bg5  O-O  6.e5  it's a very different story because now after  6...dxe5  7.dxe5  Qxd1+  , you are very happy to play  8.Rxd1  and control the d-file with your rook. }
5... c6 { Black plays a move which prevents your plan. } 6. Qd2
{ You get ready to castle queenside and  Bh6  to exchange Black's fianchettoed bishop and start an attack on the kingside.  The old strategy with  6.e5  doesn't work well here because after  6...dxe5  7.dxe5  Qxd1+  8.Rxd1  Ng4  the c6-pawn stops you from going for the Nd5 plan }
6... O-O
{ Black can also play  6...b5  , which you always counter with  7.a3  , and you can reach a transposition. }
7. Bh6 b5 8. a3
{ You stop the b-pawn from advancing!  Note that this same position can also be reached after @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/pp2ppbp/2pp1np1/6B1/3PP3/2N2N2/PPPQ1PPP/R3KB1R b KQkq - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6...b5  7.a3  O-O  8.Bh6  8.Bd3  is much more popular, but it can be beneficial to avoid blocking the d-file, as shown in this variation. }
8... Bg4 9. h4 { You go for the brutal attack! } 9... Nbd7 10. h5
{ No mercy, just go for the king! This is also the typical attacking plan against a Pirc setup. }
10... Bxh5 11. Bxg7 Kxg7 12. e5
{ This idea with e5 you always want to use at some point! } 12... dxe5 13. dxe5
Ng4 14. Rxh5
{ It's important to clear the g-file as  14.O-O-O  allows  14...Ndxe5 } 14...
gxh5 15. O-O-O
{ And now you win the knight on d7!  Because after  15...Ndxe5  16.Qg5+  wins the queen with a discovered check. }
