17. Kxg2 Qh2+ 18. Kf3 f5
{ This is always a good move in the attack. And here the computer starts going crazy and says  19.Nf6+  is the only move for White to survive. After  19.Nxd6  Qh3+  20.Kf4  Nc4!  Is the move that wins for Black with a forced mate in  17.  I didn't make this trainable because I don't want you to get accused of cheating. All jokes aside, when you think about it more, @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/p5p1/2pN3p/n4p2/5K2/3P3q/PPP1BP2/R1BQ1R2 b - - 2 20@@EndFEN@@20...Nc4  is not that illogical since after  21.dxc4  Rae8  22.Nxe8  Rxe8  , now you threaten ...Re4# and after and after  21.Nxc4  Rae8  can be played without being captured and with the threat of ... g5#. The computer here shows the importance of including all your pieces in the attack and beautifully sacrifices this seemingly useless knight on the edge of the board. }
