{ You develop the bishop as usual!   4...Be7  is a sound alternative. } 5. O-O
O-O
{ In this position, White can play a lot of moves that do not involve the c3 move for White. This makes it harder to go for the Pin setup in certain cases. }
6. h3 { A useful move that doesn't give away White's intentions yet. } 6... d5
{ Whenever you can, play ...d5! } 7. exd5 Nxd5 8. Re1
