{ Setting a trap! It is the most-played move at the top level nowadays.   8...Re8  runs into a trap since White can go for  9.d4  Nxd4  10.Nxd4  and now White wins a piece either after  10...exd4  11.Rxe8  Qxe8  12.Bxd5  or after  10...Bxd4  11.c3 }
9. c3 { If White plays c3 anyway, then the Pin-setup doesn't work anymore. }
9... h6
{ Played by Nakamura, amongst others. Your light-squared bishop is secured from any Ng5 ideas from White. }
