{ White will have to play this move sooner or later.   10.Nxe5  still doesn't work for the same reason that after  10...Nxe5  11.Rxe5  , you play  11...Bxf2+ }
10... Nf4
{ This is now a nice option. You want to trade off the light-squared bishops and play against the d3-pawn. }
11. Bxe6 { White often takes on e6, yet this was a little trap! } 11... Nxd3
{ And suddenly three pieces are hanging for White. White will have to give back more material than White initially took. }
