15. a4 a6 { An important move you claim the bishop back. } 16. Bxc6 bxc6
{ It may seem like your pawn structure has become weak now, but by trading off White's light-squared bishop, the d3-pawn has become a target. Black is already slightly better here, and all the danger in the position is gone now you have traded the light-squared bishop.  Also, your ...c6 pawn is useful because after  17.a5  , your knight can go forward with  17...Nd5   @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/1ppq2pp/pnBb4/4pp2/P7/2PP1QNP/1P3PP1/R1B1R1K1 b - - 0 16@@EndFEN@@  16...Qxc6  to trade the queens is also a good alternative. }
