{ An accurate defense against White's attack! The position is safe now, as the variation shows. }
16. Bg5 Qb6+ { The check doesn't give White time to play f6! } 17. Kh1 f6
{ Getting in this ... f6 move means that White's attack is over! Black is doing well. You can eliminate the light-squared bishop and play ...d6 to activate your bishop. }
