4. d3
{ White defends the central pawn.   4.Nc3  would transpose to the Four Knights Ruy Lopez.   4.Qe2  is an uncommon sideline, after which you can play in your regular style with  4...Bc5  5.c3  O-O  and ...Re8, ...a6, ...h6, ...d5 are the natural next moves. }
4... Bc5
