21. g3
{ White defends against the mate  After  21.Be5  Bxe5  22.Rxe5  , you can first play  22...g4  23.Qg3  and now  23...Rf6  followed by ...Ne6 when you block White's rooks on the open file. }
21... Kg8 { You unpin your knight. } 22. Re7
