{ You back up your knight with the f-pawn! While it might seem logical to advance your pawn to the center and support your knight, it's a mistake.  After  6...d5?  your other knight becomes pinned, and White can then play  7.Nxd4  .  Now White threatens Nxc6 and f3, both targeting your pinned knights. You'll find yourself in significant trouble. If you play  7...Bd7  , then after  8.Bxc6  bxc6  9.f3  , White will gain material by winning your pinned knight. }
7. Nxd4
{ White captures your pawn in the center. The knight attacks your f5-pawn, so you should trade knights. }
7... Nxd4 { You trade the knights to secure the f5-pawn } 8. Qxd4 c6
{ You're eager to advance your other pawn to the center, but the d-pawn is still pinned. It's essential to remove this pin now. Remember that your knight remains pinned, and moving it would be illegal because it's an absolute pin.  Therefore, playing  8...Bc5?  would result in losing the bishop after  9.Qxc5 }
9. Nc3
{ A powerful development move from White, which is rarely played at the Beginner level. }
9... Qf6
{ Your king is in danger, so you need to offer a trade of queens.  Capturing the bishop with  9...cxb5?  is too greedy when White blows open the position with  10.Nxe4  fxe4  11.Rxe4+  , and your king is helpless in the middle of the board.  11...Be7  would be answered with the thematic  12.Bg5  adding an attacker to the pinned bishop. }
10. Qxf6 { White's best option is to trade and go for the endgame. } 10... gxf6
11. Nxe4 fxe4 12. Rxe4+ { White captures the pawn with a check. } 12... Kf7
{ You don't want your bishop to be in the pin after  12...Be7   As this is an endgame, your king is safe here. }
13. Be2 { White threatens Bh5+ followed by Rg4 } 13... d5
{ You place your pawn in the center and control the g4-square. } 14. Bh5+ Kg7
15. Re8 { White creates a pin on your light-squared bishop and threatens Bg4! }
15... Rg8 { An important defensive move! } 16. Bg4 Bc5
{ Moving the bishop ensures your light-squared bishop is safe. } 17. Bh6+ Kh8
{ And your king is safe in the corner. } 18. Rxc8
{ White doesn't have anything better than trading the pieces. } 18... Raxc8 19.
Bxc8 Rxc8
{ Black is doing well in the endgame and will activate the king with ... Kg8-Kf7 }
