{ You can even give White another pawn. } 19. exf5+ Kf7
{ Black will go for ...Rae8 trading the rook and will win back the f5-pawn after that. With the opposite-color bishops, the endgame should be easy to defend, although White is a bit better with a pawn-up.   Trading the rooks will make defending the endgame easy, as the bishop can always guard all the pawns on the queenside without the help of the king. The king can stay on the kingside to stop White's extra pawn. }
