{ You bring the rook to the center and now threaten ...Bxf5! As you attack White's bishop now, it's no longer problematic if, after ...Bxf5, you get pinned with Rf1 as you can capture White's bishop with ...Rxe3  The computer says  17...Bxf5  was also possible, but it's risky to rush with capturing the pawn since after  18.Rf1  Kg6  19.Nf3  threatening Nh4+  19...Be4  20.Nh4+  , you would have to play  20...Kh5 }
