[Black "Scotch Schmidt Variation Four Knights: 5.Nc3 #5"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4
{ The Scotch opening! White uses the same strategy as you. } 3... exd4
{ You capture the central pawn. } 4. Nxd4
{ The mainline Scotch. White captures back the pawn in the center. } 4... Nf6
{ As is typical, you start by developing your knights and quickly exerting pressure on the center.  You're already familiar with the Scotch from playing as White and know that trading with  4...Nxd4?  5.Qxd4  isn't a good move because it helps White by letting their queen occupy a strong spot in the center. }
5. Nc3 { White develops the knight and supports the central pawn. } 5... Bb4
{ You pin the knight and pressure White's central pawn. } 6. Nxc6
{ White captures your knight. } 6... bxc6 { You recapture towards the center. }
7. Bd3 { White supports the central pawn. } 7... d5
{ You follow the first golden rule and place your pawn in the center. } 8. Bd2
{ A better move from White! You keep the same strategy to go after the e4-pawn. }
8... Bxc3 { First you eliminate the knight. } 9. Bxc3 dxe4
{ You get the central pawn. } 10. Bxf6
{ Also  10.Bc4  has sometimes been played, and White has sacrificed a pawn to have a better pawn structure and the bishop pair. I recommend to castle with  10...O-O  and with ...Be6, you get ready to trade White's light-squared bishop. }
10... Qxf6 11. Bxe4 Ba6
{ A powerful move! Before you secure your king, you make sure that White doesn't do the same. }
12. Qf3
{ White wants to exchange queens too, as the king is less safe.  Retreating with  12.Bd3  is an alternative for White, but  12...Bxd3  13.Qxd3  Black is doing well. You can either castle safely with  13...O-O  or capture the pawn with  13...Qxb2 }
12... Qxf3 13. gxf3 { White should recapture with the pawn. } 13... O-O-O
{ You still go for the queenside castle. White only has one move to survive! }
14. Rd1 { White needs to offer a trade of rooks. } 14... Kb7
{ You support the c6-pawn, While your bishop keeps restricting White's king. You can play ... g6 and ... f5 to chase away White's bishop in the center and open up the king. }
