{ A thematic move you frequently play against the Scotch aiming to get rid of this e5-pawn that was blocking your bishop. }
12. exf6 Qxe2+
{ At this point, you want to the trade queens, because here after  12...Nxf6  13.Qxe7+  you have to recapture with the king and won't be able to castle anymore. }
13. Bxe2 Nxf6 14. O-O-O O-O-O
{ Castling queenside is also good for you!  The d7-pawn needs to have some protection and after  14...O-O  White could eliminate its last defender with  15.Bxf6  Bxf6  to win the pawn with  16.Rxd7  . }
15. Rhe1 Rde8
{ You unpin your knight and move the rook to the open e-file. A typical plan is to go ...c5 and ...Bb7 to activate your light-squared bishop. }
