{ White starts hunting your knight!  White could also opt for  6.Nc3  when you can place your pawn in the center with  6...d5  and after  7.exd5  cxd5  8.Bg5  , you can stabilize the center with  8...c6 }
6... Qe7
{ You safeguard your knight by pinning the pawn. Generally, it's not ideal to position your queen in front of your bishop on an awkward square, but doing so forces White to make a similar move. Given that your queen will be attacking and White's queen will be defending, these moves work to your advantage. }
7. Qe2
{ White unpins the pawn to attack your knight again. White threatens to capture your knight again. }
7... Nd5 { You move the knight to the center. } 8. c4
{ White chases away your knight. } 8... Ba6
{ Developing the bishop and pinning the c4-pawn.  The alternative is to retreat the knight with  8...Nb6  is also fine. }
9. b3
{ After  9.Nd2  you can also play  9...g6  to develop the dark-squared bishop. }
9... g6 { You prepare to develop the dark-squared bishop. } 10. Bb2
{ White develops the bishop! } 10... Bg7
{ You develop the bishop and apply pressure on the center. } 11. g3
{ White aims to fianchetto the other bishop. Also, this position could come from the @@StartFEN@@r3kb1r/p1ppqp1p/b1p3p1/3nP3/2P5/1P6/P3QPPP/RNB1KB1R w KQkq - 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10.g3  move order. }
11... d6
{ You stay loyal to your plan of fighting and challenging the center immediately! }
12. Bg2 O-O-O 13. Qd2 Nb4 { A cool move! The knight is poisoned here! } 14. a3
Nd3+ { Sacrificing the knight as you will win back the bishop. } 15. Qxd3 Bxe5
{ You capture the pawn and open a discovered attack against the bishop! White is unable to trade because after 16.Bxe5 Qxe5+ you fork the king and rook. }
16. O-O Bxb2 { You win the bishop back and are a pawn up now. } 17. Ra2 Bg7 18.
Bxc6 d5 { A beautiful move stopping the bishop from safely moving back. } 19.
Bxd5 c6 20. Qe4
{ White still has a recourse not to lose the bishop! However, trading the queens was a big advantage for Black as the king wasn't safe. }
20... Qxe4 21. Bxe4 Kc7
{ Even though Black is a pawn down, with the bishop pair and the poor placement of White's knight Black is a bit better in the endgame. }
