16. Bc3 Bh6
{ If you could move again, you would be ready to open the position in front of White's king with  17...d5  and after  18.exd6  Rhe8  , the e-file is open, and you would be winning. Therefore, White has to measure now. }
17. c5 Qb7 18. Bxa6 Qxa6 19. Qe2
{ White needs to offer an exchange of queens as its king is in danger. } 19...
Qa3
{ You like to keep queens on the board with the safer king. At this point, the f5-pawn is hanging, and you would also like to bring your rook to the e-file with ...Rhe8 to start targeting White's vulnerable king in the center. }
