{ White develops and supports the central pawn! } 9... Bg4
{ You create a pin on the knight. } 10. Qe1 { White unpins the knight! } 10...
f6 { You aim to take down White's center and exchange the e5-pawn. } 11. exf6
Nxf6 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Ne5 Bh5
{ You keep controlling the d1-square! This makes it impossible for White to win the c6-pawn. }
