[Black "Danish Gambit #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. c3
{ The Danish Gambit! White wants to sacrifice one or two pawns for rapid development. I recommend not accepting the sacrifice but making sure you develop well. }
3... Nf6 { You develop the knight and attack White's central pawn. } 4. e5
{ White hunts your knight. } 4... Nd5
{ You go to a safe square in the center. } 5. cxd4
{ After  5.Qxd4  You have two options! One plan is to go after White's central pawn on e5, which is far advanced. You can start with  5...Ne7  followed by ...Ng6, after which ...Nc6 attacks the queen, the central pawn. }
5... d6
{ You attack White's central pawn!  After  6.Nf3  Nc6  you transpose to the Göring Gambit. }
