1. e4 e5 2. f4 { The King's Gambit. } 2... exf4
{ You capture the pawn and accept the challenge. } 3. Bc4
{ White develops the bishop! And this is one of the variations that is unsound but where White aims to take trick you in unfamilair theory. Take care for the next move! }
3... Nc6
{ You aim to transpose to the mainline with the knight move first.  Now after  4.Nf3  the most popular move you play  4...g5  and you are back in business as you transpose to the lines you will learn here.  You don't start with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/8/2B1Pp2/8/PPPP2PP/RNBQK1NR b KQkq - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3...g5  here because  4.h4  is annoying! In the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/8/4Pp2/8/PPPP2PP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  line after  3...g5  4.h4  you can play  4...g4  attacking the knight.  After @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/8/4Pp2/8/PPPP2PP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Bc4  g5?  4.h4  now  4...g4  doesn't do anything, and after  5.d4  White has a dominating center. For the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/8/4Pp2/8/PPPP2PP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  line, you don't want to start with  3...Nc6  because after  4.d4  g5  , White plays  5.d5  to kick your knight back. }
4. d4 Nf6
{ You develop your knights first, as usual, and put pressure on White's center!  You don't have to fear any knight hunts since  5.d5?  is countered with  5...Ne5  attacking the bishop and  5.e5  with a standard  5...d5   After @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/8/2BPPp2/8/PPP3PP/RNBQK1NR b KQkq d3 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4...g5?  5.h4  is still strong! }
5. e5 d5
{ This is the thematic reply like you play against the Scotch Gambit and you are already doing great here. }
6. Bb5
{ White still can't both regain the f4-pawn and also pin your knight.  Instead White would have to play  6.Be2  to defend against these tactics but after  6...Ne4  7.Bxf4  , you have different good ways to continue the break with  7...f6  is an option, but also developing with  7...Be6  would be good. }
6... Ne4 7. Bxf4 Qh4+ { Forking the king and bishop. } 8. g3 Nxg3
{ And you will win the rook with this tactic! Both the pawn and bishop are pinned. }
9. Bxg3 Qe4+ { Your queen keeps forking! } 10. Kf2 Qxh1
{ You won the rook, and your queen will be safe! } *

