9... Be7 { You develop your bishop and get ready to castle. } 10. Be2 O-O 11.
O-O a6
{ You aim for the same plan! ...b5, ...Na5, ...Nc4 going after the a3-pawn. }
12. Bb2 b5 13. Qd2
{ The best approach for White would be to prepare and push the d-pawn forward. After  13.d5  exd5  14.exd5  Na5  you can aim for Bb7 attacking the d5-pawn. }
13... Na5 { You follow the same plan. } 14. Rad1 Nc4
{ You go for the knight jump and exchange White's good bishop. } 15. Bxc4 bxc4
16. d5 exd5 17. exd5 Bd6
{ It's always important to immediately block that d-pawn. } 18. Qd4
{ White could win a pawn. But with the bishop pair and the d-pawn securely blocked, this is fine. }
18... f6 { Blocking the mate and restricting the knight. } 19. Qxc4 Bd7
{ A safe position! You can activate the rooks and aim to pressure the bishop and the weak a3 and d5-pawn. }
