13... f5
{ Let's now allow White to get another strong bishop! You want to chase the knight back to c3, where it blocks the square for the dark-squared bishop. So after  14.Nc3  Rb8  is strong attacking the b2-pawn.  After @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/p3b1pp/2p1p3/5p2/2p1N1n1/6P1/PP1BPPBP/R2R2K1 w - f6 0 14@@EndFEN@@  14.h3  , it's both fine to capture or move the knight back. The idea you can remember is that after a possible continuation with  14...fxe4  15.hxg4  Bf6  16.Bc3  e3  17.f4  Rb8  18.Bxc6  , you can sacrifice the exchange with  18...Rxb2!  19.Bxb2  Bxb2  and your c-pawn will start running }
