[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3
{ The Catalan! An opening where White aims to create a powerful light-squared bishop.  This position can also be reached from the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.g3  Nf6  4.Nf3  move order }
4... dxc4 { You capture the pawn. } 5. Bg2 c5
{ As typical for the d4-openings. You want to play your c-pawn first before placing your knight on c6 so that you can apply pressure on the center. }
6. O-O { White castles and is quick with development. } 6... Nc6
{ You develop the knight as usual. } 7. Qa4
{ A critical variation! White creates a pin on your knight. } 7... Bd7
{ You unpin the knight. Capturing the central pawn with  7...cxd4  runs into  8.Nxd4  when White has three attackers on your pinned knight. This still has been played quite some times, however, after  8...Qxd4  9.Bxc6+  , you are unable to capture the bishop back since White would fork your king and rook, so after  9...Bd7  10.Rd1  Bxc6  11.Qxc6+  bxc6  12.Rxd4  White has a better endgame because of Black's broken pawn structure on the queenside. }
8. dxc5 Na5
{ You counterattack the queen and defend the c4-pawn.  Also, it would be fine to recapture with  8...Bxc5  , but keep your pawn with  8...Na5  is more ambitious. }
9. Qa3 Rc8 10. Be3
{ This is a bit of a passive move from White, so you can start attacking. }
10... Nd5 { Your standard reaction is challenging the bishop. } 11. Ne5
{ A difficult move for White to play. } 11... Nxe3 12. fxe3 Rxc5 13. Nxf7
{ White forks the queen and rook; it's time to strike back with a discovered attack. }
13... Rf5 { Discovered attack on the queen. } 14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15. Qxd6 Rxf1+
{ The trade forces the Catalan bishop off the powerful diagonal since  16.Kxf1?  allows  16...Qf6+  forking the king and the b2-pawn. }
16. Bxf1 Bc6
{ When White's bishop goes away, you take over the diagonal. You are happy to sacrifice the e6-pawn since after. }
17. Qxe6+ Qe7 18. Qxe7+ Kxe7
{ You are ready to activate your rook with ...Rd8 and enter the back rank or the second rank. }
