{ You can castle and don't have to be afraid to get your rook trapped. } 12.
Nc7 { White is feeling greedy and going after the rook. } 12... e5
{ It's time to counterattack. } 13. Bxe5 Nc6
{ The knight develops and also attacks the bishop. } 14. Bxf6
{ White needs to trade and capture the rook after if they want to go for the material. }
14... Bxf6 15. Nxa8
{ White managed to capture the rook but they will pay a big price for it. }
15... Bxb2 { You strike back. } 16. Rb1 Qxe3+
{ You capture another pawn and this time with a check. } 17. Be2 Bc3+
{ This check makes sure White can no longer castle. } 18. Kf1 Bd4
{ You threaten mate. } 19. Qe1 Rxa8
{ You win the knight back! White's pieces are so passive. You are in a better position with Black despite still being down an exchange for a pawn. }
