{ I recommend this move to make sure you can win the pawn back later.   6...Nc6!?  also looked like an interesting option but after  6...Nc6  7.Nxd5  e5  8.Bg5  Qa5+  9.Nc3  Bxc5  10.a3  Be7  you have some compensation for the pawn but it feels like it's not enough. }
7. Qd2 Nc6
{ You can develop your knight! There is no rush to capture the pawn back immediately. }
8. Bg5 { White could play this to avoid that ...e5 comes with tempo. } 8...
Qxc5
{ You capture back the pawn.  Going for  9.Bxf6?  gxf6  10.Nxd5  is dangerous for White since after  10...O-O-O  you get strong counterplay on the d-file. }
9. O-O-O e6
{ You secure your pawns. You can continue with ...Rc8 putting pressure on the c-file. Your king coud be very safe later with a kingside castle but can in some cases also be safe in the center on e7 and shelter behind the pawns. }
