{ You offer the trade of queens with a winning position.  After  21.Qh5  , it's good to defend with  21...Ra7!  As you are already two pieces up, you can give the bishop back to defend. Being materialistic with  21...Bc7?  could give White some counter chances by going for  22.Rf1  when they aim to play Rf4-Rg4 and pin your queen. }
