{ White wants to start trading the pieces with Ne5, so you kick the bishop back.  After  11...Bd6  would also have been possible, but I don't recommend it to stay consistent because in the @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp3ppp/2n2n2/2p5/2Pp4/1P3NP1/P2P1PBP/RNBQ1RK1 w kq - 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9.d3  Be7  10.Bf4  variation  10...Bd6  runs into  11.Re1+   To @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp3ppp/2n2n2/2p5/2Pp4/1P3NP1/P2P1PBP/RNBQ1RK1 w kq - 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9.d3  Be7  10.Bf4  , you reply in the same fashion with  10...Nh5  White's best move is  11.Ne5  , which allows you to destroy the pawn structure with  11...Nxf4  12.Nxc6  bxc6  13.Bxc6+  Bd7  14.Bxd7  Qxd7  15.gxf4  and after  15...Qh3  You can aim to attack with ...a5 and a rooklift }
