7. e4 dxe4
{ As usual, you trade the pawns in the center when they are facing! This way, you can avoid some closed KID structures your opponent is more familiar with.   7...d4  is also an option. It makes sure Black has more space but also gives away the beautiful c4-square for White's knight. You know the rule when pawns are facing in the center, so you don't have to think about this option. }
