[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "15a) English Reti and Sidelines"]
[Black "Grob Opening: 1.g4 #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. g4 d5 { As usual against the sidelines! } 2. Bg2 e5
{ You occupy the full center!   2...Bxg4  is also possible but is what White hopes for as after  3.c4  e6  , they could create an attack with  4.Qb3 }
3. d4 { Going for a direct break in the center would be best for White. } 3...
exd4 { You trade the pawns as usual! } 4. Qxd4 Be6
{ You defend the central pawn and develop the bishop! } 5. Nc3 Nc6
{ You develop the knight and gain a tempo on the queen. } 6. Qa4 Nf6
{ You develop the knight as usual to the natural square. } 7. g5
{ White kicks the knight! } 7... Nd7
{ You move back to unpin your other knight. } 8. Nxd5
{ White captures the pawn!   8.Bxd5  would already lose the piece for White after  8...Bxd5  9.Nxd5  Nc5  10.Qc4  b5  White has no way to keep defending the knight in the center. }
8... Nc5 { You attack the queen and give a discovered attack on the knight. }
9. Qc4 { White's only move is to defend the knight and run into a pin. } 9...
Qd7
{ You prepare to castle queenside and add another attacker to the pinned knight. }
10. e4 { White can also immediately add a defender to the pinned knight. }
10... O-O-O { Castling increases the pressure on the knight. } 11. Ne2
{ White prepares to defend the knight more. } 11... Nxe4
{ You eliminate the defender to win back the pawn.  After  12.Bxe4  Bxd5  13.Bxd5  Qxd5  14.Qxd5  Rxd5  White has a weak g5 and c2-pawns, and Black is doing great in the endgame. }
12. Nef4 { White supports the knight! } 12... Bb4+
{ It's time to start developing fast! } 13. c3 Rhe8
{ Active play! Since White's king is still on the e-file, it would be way too dangerous for White to capture your bishop now.   14.cxb4  Bxd5  clears the e-file and after  15.Qxd5  Nc3+  wins the queen with the discovered attack. }
14. O-O { White castles to get out of the attack! } 14... Bxd5
{ It's time to capture everything. } 15. Nxd5 Qxd5 16. Qxd5 Rxd5 17. Re1
{ A cunning move from White! By creating a pin, White wants to win back the piece without giving up a pawn for it. }
17... Bc5 { You move the bishop away! } 18. Bxe4
{ White has to be brave and capture the pawn, allowing you to pin the bishop! }
18... Rde5 19. Bf5+ { A last tactical recourse saves the bishop for White. }
19... Kb8 20. Rxe5 Rxe5 21. Bxh7
{ White has to be brave and capture the pawn, allowing you to keep the bishop almost trapped. }
21... g6
{ You keep the bishop caught on h7! Next, you can aim for ...Re2 targetting the f2-pawn }
