{ White now has the chance to trap the queen and not allow you to castle. In case it's not problematic, since you immediately get counterplay in the endgame. }
11... Nb4 12. Qxd8+ Kxd8 { You threaten to trap the rook with ... Nc2 } 13. Nc3
Ke7
{ Your king is always safe in the center on e7. Next, you can play ...Rd8, getting your rook to the open d-file. }
