9. Bxg7 { White accepts the pawn sacrifice. } 9... Rg8
{ You activate your rook on the open g-file and kick the bishop back. } 10. Bb2
Qe7 { You get ready for a queenside castle! You are ahead in development. } 11.
Nc3 { White gets the knight out! } 11... Nxc3
{ You trade the knight as usual! } 12. Bxc3 O-O-O
{ You castle queenside and finish your development. } 13. Rc1 Kb8
{ You can first safeguard your king! Also, 13...e5 would be a good option. }
14. d4
{ When White places the pawn in the center, you can reply in the same way as before. }
14... cxd4 15. exd4 e5 { You challenge the pawn in the center! } 16. dxe5 Bh3
{ This keeps being a powerful reply! White is unable to capture your dark-squared bishop because you threaten ...Bxg2-Bf3# }
17. g3 Bxe5
{ You win the pawn back and go for a discovered check on the queen. } 18. Bd2
Bxf1 { You win the exchange. } 19. Qxf1 Nd4
{ You avoid that White captures your knight and weakens your pawn structure. }
20. Nxd4 Rxd4
{ You capture back with a fighting middle game position.  Also  20...Bxd4  would have been good. In this position, you would be happy to trade the dark-squared bishop if possible }
